A request from @RahulRaman

This LyCORIS has been trained after carefully selecting some images of screenshots from Flashdance movie. All photos have been enhanced to make the most of them. I hope you like it!

CFG scale should be between 4-7.

LyCORIS weights should be between 0.9-1.2

Keerthy Suresh (born 17 October 1992) is an Indian actress who appears predominantly in Tamil, Telugu and Malayalam films. A recipient of various accolades including a National Film Award, three SIIMA Awards and a Filmfare Award South, Keerthy was placed in Forbes India's 30 Under 30 list of 2021.

Keerthy is the daughter of film producer G. Suresh Kumar and actress Menaka G. Suresh. She began her career as a child actress in the early 2000s and returned to films after studying fashion design. She had her first lead role in the 2013 Malayalam film Geethaanjali, for which she won SIIMA Award for Best Female Debut – Malayalam.

After winning SIIMA Award for Best Female Debut – Tamil for Idhu Enna Maayam (2015), Keerthy went on to star in successful films such as Ring Master (2014), Nenu Sailaja (2016), Rajinimurugan (2016), Remo (2016), Bairavaa (2017), Nenu Local (2017), Mahanati (2018), Sarkar (2018), Thaanaa Serndha Koottam (2018), Penguin (2020), Miss India (2021), Good Luck Sakhi (2022) and Sarkaru Vaari Paata (2022). Keerthy received the Filmfare Award for Best Actress – Telugu nomination for Nenu Sailaja and Mahanati, winning for the latter, which also fetched her the National Film Award for Best Actress.

items.name: ShadowGost
items.description:
Information - ShadowGost

ShadowGost, this model is the one that I have dedicated more work, I really liked the publications on Twitter about characters or landscapes that had a good management of lighting and shadows, I always had problems with generating a good composition so I ended up creating this model.

If you want to see more results or know about future models that I will be publishing you can visit me in my social networks, it will help me a lot and you can buy me a coffee to support this content.

Recommendations for use

After several attempts, (I still need to learn more) you can improve the models to make it easier to generate beautiful images.

Shadows and Highlights Handling.

The mainstay of all this is compositing a good prompt (or that's what worked for me).

  • First I detail the quality with tags like (Masterpiece, extremely detailed fine touch).

  • Second, the shadows these tags generate a good result (hard light, studio light, light rays, dappled light, reflection, shadows, ray tracing) depending on the environment you want to develop you can use (warm light, sunlight, natural light).

  • And finally, character development, this is at the convenience of each user, although I always add this tag for its versatility (dynamic pose).

It is recommended to use Hiresfix, if you want instant results, but without it also generates beautiful works.

Image tips:

  • If you are going to generate images with a large resolution or the character you develop is far away I recommend you to use Hires.fix, to improve the quality.

  • Addetailer is a good option if you don't use Hires.fix and improves the details of your image.

  • If you want to get a brush or watercolor painting effect you can use this setting with Hires.fix:

    • Upscaler: Latent

    • Hirest steps: 15 - 20

    • Denoising strength: 0.46 - 0.5

Recommended parameters:

  • Sampler: DPM++ SDE Karras: 20 to 30 steps.

  • Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras: 20 to 60 steps.

  • Sampler: Euler a: 40 to 60 steps.

  • CFG Scale: 4 to 11.

  • Resolutions: 512x768, 512x1024 for Portrait!

  • Resolutions: 768x512, 1024x512, 1536x512 for Landscape!

  • Hires.fix: Latent, Lanczos, R-ESRGAN 4x+Anime6b.

  • Clip Skip: 2.

  • Negatives: ' (worst quality, low quality:1.4), (zombie, sketch, interlocked fingers, comic) '

  • Negatives if you can't use Hires.fix:
    '(worst quality:1.6, low quality:1.6), (zombie, sketch, interlocked fingers, comic)'

items.name: Shidoshi Fun Mix
items.description:
Added version 1.9. Someone requested 1.2, but I think this one is better. This is a pruned model. Read more:

Same advice as version 1.0 (read below). Images were generated using Vladmandic's SD.Next (updated daily, latest features and much faster than A1111).

I find with these mixes, less is better and tuning the prompts once you have something close. Adding a 100 word negative prompt usually makes it look like crap. Same goes with the positive prompt. Adding too much strength to stuff like, "(8k, absurdres, WOW, INCREDIBLE DETAIL, Nikon DS500 120 gigapixel:1.8)", will also make it look like crap.

I start with "Masterpiece" in the positive prompt and "(worst quality:2.0), (low quality:1.8), (normal quality:1.6)" in the negative prompt.

This model is semi-realistic, so I don't think adding camera models will make it look better? Try it... I don't know.

I also I tried the online generator supplied by civitai. Output is garbage. Recommend generating locally on your own GPU.

Also if anyone wants the full float of this for their own mixing purposes, I'll upload it.

So, I decided to make a mix new model (non-SD XL). I guess it's what you'd call a semi-realistic model.

It's based off my original Shidoshi mix, added some of PSoft's lora's (fat man, ugly man, etc... Best loras on here), added some other hentai models using training difference add, mixed some more, and so on.

I think the result is "fun". So I called it "Fun Mix".

Try it out and post some samples.

No VAE burned in. Use vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned.

Some advice:

Recommended neg: (worst quality, low quality, normal quality:1.8) -- Try different strengths. i.e. 1.4, 1.6, 2.0. Also for 1.9: (worst quality:2.0), (low quality:1.8), (normal quality:1.6), (stepping it seems like it has better results).

Sampling: I use DPM++ 2M SDE on first pass (30 steps). I follow up on second pass/ hires fix using DPM++ 2M SDE Karras with higher steps.

Clip skip: Either 1 or 2. 1 Works fine.

CFG scale: Keep low. 6-8. Oversaturation occurs at 9.5+ or use "Dynamic Thresholding". v1.9 Seems to work at 11.0+ at times.

Thanks and enjoy. I like feedback and post some samples!

items.name: NightVision XL - Photorealistic | Portrait | Photography | Hyperreal | Architecture | Interior Design - No refiner needed!
items.description:
Like the work I do and want to help support me? Buy me a coffee! ☕️🫶🏼

This is NightVision XL, a lightly trained base SDXL model that is then further refined with community LORAs to get it to where it is now. NightVision XL has been refined and biased to produce touched-up photorealistic portrait output that is ready-stylized for Social media posting! NightVision XL has nice coherency and is avoiding some of the weird body issues and biases that are starting to plague some of the other photorealistic models. Further, NightVision XL produces rich deep blacks and great evening/night time scenes. It can also produce ridiculously bright output as well!

NightVision XL is capable of both SFW and NSFW output. As with all of my other models, tools and embeddings, NightVision XL is easy to use, preferring simple prompts and letting the model do the heavy lifting for scene building.

NOTE - This version includes a baked VAE, no need to download or use the "suggested" external VAE.

WARNING - DO NOT USE SDXL REFINER WITH NIGHTVISION XL

The SDXL refiner is incompatible and you will have reduced quality output if you try to use the base model refiner with NightVision XL.

Follow me here by clicking the heart ❤️ and liking the model 👍, and you will be notified of any future versions I release. modelVersions.name: V0.7.4.3-release-bakedVAE
modelVersions.description:
NightVision XL 0.7.4.3 Release Notes

With this version of NightVision XL, you should notice more natural and normal looking bodies, a bit more facial variety, and much more balanced color output vs 0.7.0.2. Bodies also look better naked, with less noticeable shoulder bone caps on very thin subjects, more natural ribs on less thin subjects, and even more natural features on skin like moles, blemishes and stretch marks, and old people actually look old. Something I've noticed anecdotally but haven't tested in detail is that blood on skin (like a bloody lip or a cut for example) looks much more natural and realistic, and water looks more wet and less like painted on glue, however YMMV.

Bodies should now look much better proportioned and much less waifish and stretched out, especially in tall AR images. To be clear, while it's not 100% fixed, I've put a lot of work into trying to fix the stretchy giraffe necks, weirdly long legs and freaky torsos that all of the community models have inherited from base. While I haven't banished it completely, it seems body balance is MUCH better. Further, while the default output of this model continues to be photorealism biased, the model is much less rigid now, and you should be able to achieve other styles such as line art or anime (and more) with just a bit of style prompting.

TLDR Improvements

  • body shapes are much more natural, even in non-square ARs

  • more natural looking skin

  • less rigid, can produce other styles than photoreal much easier now

  • less close up portrait bias

  • Output is less contrasty than 0.7.0.2 and colors are more balanced than 0.6.8.1

09/11/23 Changelog

Backmerges into 0.6.8.1 and 0.6.5.0, and differential merges with (internal only version) 0.7.3.3 which was a WIP model. Added 2 new community loras and an internal fixer lora.

New Community LORAs added

  • polyhedron_all_sdxl

  • NaturalBody

New Internal LORA Added

  • nf_v3-test

Internal LORA Rebalance

  • Nightshift

modelVersions.name: Beta_0.7.0.2-BakedVAE
modelVersions.description:
NightVision XL Beta 0.7.0.2 Release Notes 08/30/23

This version has been updated with a light fine tuning I trained on several hundred analog photographs with hopes to keep improving eyes, teeth and skin details, continuing to chase the dragon of fine photography style output. Version 0.7.0.2 seems to operate best in the 4 - 6 CFG range, with color pop really hitting around 7.5 or so, but can push into crushed blacks/whites. I'm noticing a nice film grain effect on darker images now, and overall coherence seems to have been improved.

Known Issues

  • Hands are improving, but still luck of the seed

  • color temperature has changed a bit since 0.6.8.1, may be a bit more contrasty. I've gotten good feedback from testers on the color, but it is less "neutral" - This is really only noticeable if you're doing after-work in PS/LR and are playing with color temp values, and it's not bad, just different.

  • male genitalia still non-existent - Every attempt to fix penises so far has lead to coherence problems (and tends to put them everywhere)

  • Stretchy nude bodies - long torsos, overly long legs, long necks - This is an issue that comes all the way up from base, but I'm going to start tracking it here as I want to try to banish it in future versions.

modelVersions.name: Beta_0.6.8.1-BakedVAE
modelVersions.description:
NightVision Beta 0.6.8.1 Release Notes

I'm happy to release the latest version of NightVision Beta to the public! This has been in testing for about a week with internal testers, and they've been having a ball with it, so I'm looking forward to seeing all the great art everybody can create with it!

  • Coherence Boost: Improved overall coherence for a smoother user experience.

  • Facial Detail & Variety: Enhanced facial features, adding more detail and variety.

  • Background Detail & Variety: Increased detail and diversity in background elements.

  • Better Hands & Eyes: Refined hands and eyes for a more natural appearance.

  • Improved Object Interaction: Characters now hold objects more convincingly.

  • Skin Detail: Significant improvement in skin texture and appearance.

  • Dirt, Grime & "Lived-in" Feeling: Added realism with better rendering of dirt, grime, and a more "lived-in" look.

LORAs Added

  • xl_real_beta

  • Grit-SDXL

  • MovieStillMasteryV03

  • LORAs rebalanced

  • Black_Sa_May

modelVersions.name: Alpha_0.6.5.0-BakedVAE
modelVersions.description:
Nightvision XL Alpha 0.6.5.0 Release Notes 08/16/23

This new release should hopefully fix (or mostly fix) the nipples on the outside of clothes issue that was showing up in 0.5.2. It should also have more facial variety, better response to cinematic terms like LUT and color temperature, and should maintain the nice creamy dark images that NightVision is designed to produce. Finally, and this is a big one, I've added more facial variety to the output, which should stave off some of the biases that are starting to show up more prominently in other realistic models (mostly Asian / female / body shape bias). I'm also continuing to try to improve eyes and teeth.

0.6.50 Changelog

  • Added new LORAs

    • pfac (Realistic_Human_Face_portraits_XL)

    • TeethXL

  • Rebalanced nurlens_SDXL_V0.1, MovieStillXLV7 Black_Sa_May and SDXL_TeethXL

Known Issues

  • Hands

  • Penises

  • teeth and eyes at a distance can look off

  • NSFW may be a bit harder to make happen, and women's anatomy may have taken a small hit with trying to fix the nipple issues. Can still produce artful nudes just fine, but porn output may be affected.

This is the first release version of NightVisionXL (NVXL) - NVXL is designed to produce photorealistic portrait output with simple prompting producing gorgeous, social media ready output. NVXL can produce both SFW and artistic NSFW imagery, and can be further enhanced using SDXL compatible LORAs, including the porn LORAs if you're so inclined.

Changelog Notes

modelVersions.name: Alpha_0.1.0.0-BakedVAE
modelVersions.description:
Alpha Version 0.1.0.0 Release Notes

I'm uploading my original fine tuning of Base SDXL for NightVision, just so I can change the label on the listing from "merged" to "trained", as all of the merges were on top of this original tuning. I am only doing this for contest eligibility, this is an inferior version of NightVision compared to ANY of the other versions I have already listed here. This was trained on 1,000 hand captioned images selected for their realism, dynamic range and photographic style, which is the core of what NightVision XL does.

This version biases towards portrait photography, but the bias is slight and can be pushed into other styles pretty easily via prompting. Eyes are bad, hands are bad, NSFW is really difficult to make happen as none of the training images were nude.

This is a pruned fp16 version with the fixed SDXL_VAE in.

Known Issues

  • Eyes are nightmare level bad at anything other than close range

  • hands are a travesty

  • NSFW is very difficult to make happen

  • Realistic style is very "wobbly" - unlike later versions of NightVision, you may have to prompt for realism if it's falling back into other styles.

This is a compliance model for contest eligibility, please don't feel pressured to download it! =)

items.name: SDXL Compositing Images Workflow (ComfyUI)
items.description:
While we're waiting for SDXL ControlNet Inpainting for ComfyUI, here's a decent alternative. It allows you to create a separate background and foreground using basic masking. Works VERY well!.

Version 4 includes 4 different workflows based on your needs!

PRE-REQUISITES

  • WAS Node Suite

  • Impact Pack

  • Node Nesting module

  • Masquerade Nodes

  • Mile High Styler

INSTALLATION

  • Go to Comfy Manager -> Fetch Updates -> Install Custom Nodes for any missing custom nodes

  • Enter Prompt for Subject 1

  • Enter prompt for Subject 2 that will be pasted into Subject 1's scene

  • In the preview box "Mask LOCATION for Subject 2" mask out the area where you want your second subject to be pasted (it will automatically be resized to fit the area you mask

  • In the preview box "Mask Cut out Subject 2", use SAM Detector or mask out the area you want to cut and paste into other image's scene

  • Enter prompt that describes the full scene under the "Check Placement" area

  • You may want to cancel the render a few times while you tweak your settings, but this is a VERY quick/efficient workflow

items.name: Yoko Tsuno
items.description:
Yoko Tsuno character, from the same name graphic novel by Roger Leloup.

This Lora is intended to generate her only, I've had poor results trying to integrate the others.

Lots of pre-processing with this one. Few usable images, and old posters to restore. But it's working - just you'll always get her 1980-1990 look. No other adaptation has been made at this point of writing and there are even fewer fanarts so it will stick to the graphic novel style no matter what.

I honestly have no idea what could be the best model(s) for this one, but i guess any semi-anime will do. I've had pretty good results with PorcelainEarthMix so sticking with this one. It also seem to be the easiest to control face rendering with.

  • Trained Word: Yoko Tsuno

  • SFW only - integrating NSFW in the dataset may degrade overall quality, especially face

  • Dataset size: 44 images

  • Can draw both her Earth outfits as well as bodysuits/spacesuits, very good at adding space helmets without any other lora/lyco

  • Can change outfit color palette (to some extent)

  • Reinforcement tags: Short Black Hair, Hairband, Traditional Media, Science Fiction, Retro Artstyle, 1980s \(style\), 1990s \(style\)
    For Earth outfits: Red Dress, Black Pants, Kimono, Obi, Cheongsem (this one is unstable)
    For space outfits: bodysuit, spacesuit, space helmet, futuristic

  • Optimal weight range: 0.9 - 1

Some of the samples try to draw distant relatives of the scenes from the original, the others are completely random mashups. Maybe you shouldn't play with Monya's time machine in secret...

(Bows are hard, mkay ?)

Extra resources used not listed in generation data:
Unlimited Blade Works: https://civitai.com/models/69323
Bowser: https://civitai.com/models/7300
Princess Peach: https://civitai.com/models/16250
Tron Style embedding: https://civitai.com/models/4317

Hope you like it, and have fun :)
